name: beep
description: Play a beeping sound.

name: cursorTo
description:
Moves the cursor to the specified `row` and `column`.

Though the ANSI Control Sequence for Cursor Position is `1`-based, this
method takes row and column values starting from `0` and adjusts them to `1`-
based values.
signature: declare const cursorTo: (column: number, row?: number) => Ansi

name: cursorMove
description:
Move the cursor position the specified number of `rows` and `columns`
relative to the current cursor position.

If the cursor is already at the edge of the screen in either direction, then
additional movement will have no effect.
signature: declare const cursorMove: (column: number, row?: number) => Ansi

name: cursorUp
description:
Moves the cursor up by the specified number of `lines` (default `1`) relative
to the current cursor position.

If the cursor is already at the edge of the screen, this has no effect.

name: cursorDown
description:
Moves the cursor down by the specified number of `lines` (default `1`)
relative to the current cursor position.

If the cursor is already at the edge of the screen, this has no effect.

name: cursorForward
description:
Moves the cursor forward by the specified number of `columns` (default `1`)
relative to the current cursor position.

If the cursor is already at the edge of the screen, this has no effect.

name: cursorBackward
description:
Moves the cursor backward by the specified number of `columns` (default `1`)
relative to the current cursor position.

If the cursor is already at the edge of the screen, this has no effect.

name: cursorLeft
description: Moves the cursor to the first column of the current row.

name: cursorSavePosition
description: Saves the cursor position, encoding shift state and formatting attributes.

name: cursorRestorePosition
description:
Restores the cursor position, encoding shift state and formatting attributes
from the previous save, if any, otherwise resets these all to their defaults.

name: cursorNextLine
description:
Moves cursor to beginning of the line the specified number of rows down
(default `1`).

name: cursorPrevLine
description:
Moves cursor to beginning of the line the specified number of rows up
(default `1`).

name: cursorHide
description: Hides the cursor.

name: cursorShow
description: Shows the cursor.

name: eraseLines
description: Erase from the current cursor position up the specified amount of rows.

name: eraseEndLine
description:
Clears from the current cursor position to the end of the current line.

The current cursor position does not change.

name: eraseStartLine
description:
Clears from the current cursor position to the start of the current line.

The current cursor position does not change.

name: eraseLine
description:
Clears the current line.

The current cursor position does not change.

name: eraseDown
description:
Clears from the current cursor position to the end of the screen.

The current cursor position does not change.

name: eraseUp
description:
Clears from the current cursor position to the beginning of the screen.

The current cursor position does not change.

name: eraseScreen
description: Clears the entire screen and move the cursor to the upper left.

name: combine
signature: declare const combine: { (that: Ansi): (self: Ansi) => Ansi; (self: Ansi, that: Ansi): Ansi; }
